<i>- maya?</i>

14:40.647 --> 14:42.580
Nope, me.

14:46.452 --> 14:48.386
( sighs )
told more truths,

14:48.388 --> 14:49.787
Did ya?

14:49.789 --> 14:51.656
Well, the thing I probably
should have mentioned

14:51.658 --> 14:55.460
Is I've never understood
the universe at all.

14:56.795 --> 14:59.063
The universe is upside down.

14:59.065 --> 15:01.432
I lied to farkle,
he loves me.

15:01.434 --> 15:03.434
I told maya the truth,

15:03.436 --> 15:05.169
She went out the window.

15:05.171 --> 15:06.704
Upside down!
You here me?

15:06.706 --> 15:08.106
<i>( creaking )</i>

15:08.108 --> 15:10.174
Hey.

15:10.176 --> 15:12.210
Well, now she's back.

15:12.212 --> 15:15.079
Maybe it's
not as upside down
as you think.

15:15.814 --> 15:17.315
It's a nice locket, maya.

15:17.317 --> 15:19.117
Thanks, mr. Matthews.

15:19.119 --> 15:22.253
It looks like someone else's
expensive gold locket.

15:22.255 --> 15:23.721
Maybe it is.

15:23.723 --> 15:25.490
But, you know,
I don't think

15:25.492 --> 15:28.192
- That matters
to maya at all.
- You don't?

15:28.194 --> 15:30.762
You know, it's an interesting
thing about lockets.

15:30.764 --> 15:33.131
It's usually
what's in the inside

15:33.133 --> 15:35.166
That matters most
to people.

15:35.168 --> 15:37.235
Isn't that right, maya?

15:47.346 --> 15:48.513
Yeah, okay.

15:52.351 --> 15:53.851
Please don't tell anyone

15:53.853 --> 15:55.753
This is how I live
in my own house.

16:03.562 --> 16:04.862
What's inside
the locket, maya,

16:04.864 --> 16:06.164
That's so important
to you?

16:11.770 --> 16:13.371
Who is this family?

16:13.373 --> 16:15.139
I don't know.

16:15.141 --> 16:17.241
( breathes deeply )
a father,

16:17.243 --> 16:18.643
A mother

16:18.645 --> 16:19.911
And a little girl.

16:19.913 --> 16:22.280
I just like that
they're all together.

16:22.282 --> 16:24.716
I'm keeping it.

16:24.718 --> 16:26.617
Oh, boy.

16:31.223 --> 16:33.324
She's at the front door too.

16:34.793 --> 16:36.461
It's like there's
two of her.

16:37.730 --> 16:39.297
- ( mimics motor whir )
- ( cory screams )

16:49.241 --> 16:51.709
So what do we do now?
Just sit here or what?

16:53.412 --> 16:55.346
Hey, dad.
Can you tell me

16:55.348 --> 16:57.415
Why I kind of think
trying to help farkle

16:57.417 --> 16:59.183
May have been wrong

16:59.185 --> 17:01.285
And maybe maya
should keep the locket?

17:01.287 --> 17:01.986
I should?

17:01.988 --> 17:04.589
Maybe.

17:04.591 --> 17:06.791
Is it me
that's upside down?

17:07.960 --> 17:10.228
You know what, girls?

17:10.230 --> 17:11.295
The universe is the most

17:11.297 --> 17:13.331
Confusing place
you'll ever live.

17:15.868 --> 17:17.635
But if you listen carefully,

17:17.637 --> 17:20.271
You'll find out
that it's paying attention

17:20.273 --> 17:22.473
And that it cares about you.

17:24.276 --> 17:25.843
Is that the truth?

17:25.845 --> 17:28.579
It's the only one
I'm still sure of.

17:31.550 --> 17:33.851
Hey, auggie,
is that for me, buddy?

17:33.853 --> 17:35.420
I made it for you.

17:35.422 --> 17:38.489
Oh, auggie,
thank you so much.

17:38.491 --> 17:40.224
Thank you.

17:40.226 --> 17:42.593
Look at this, ooh.

17:42.595 --> 17:44.762
This looks good.

17:47.399 --> 17:50.568
It's-- it's cold s'ghetti.

17:50.570 --> 17:51.969
I know it's better warmer,

17:51.971 --> 17:54.272
But I don't know
how to do that.

17:55.674 --> 17:57.775
Auggie, I appreciate

17:57.777 --> 17:59.911
That you did
anything for me at all.

17:59.913 --> 18:02.313
You said that
very nice.

18:02.315 --> 18:04.315
Why didn't you say it
that way to mom?

18:06.518 --> 18:08.920
What?  But all I did
was tell mom the truth.

18:08.922 --> 18:11.556
Then why do you get
cold s'ghetti?

18:13.559 --> 18:15.893
Both: Whoa.

18:15.895 --> 18:17.829
Whoa.

18:19.431 --> 18:21.332
Auggie, are you saying

18:21.334 --> 18:22.633
The truth doesn't matter

18:22.635 --> 18:24.035
As much as
how you treat people?

18:24.037 --> 18:27.271
Auggie, are you saying
that the truth does matter,

18:27.273 --> 18:28.606
But you should tell it
to people warmly?

18:28.608 --> 18:30.308
Maya:  <i>Auggie,</i>

18:30.310 --> 18:31.776
Are you saying
that the universe

18:31.778 --> 18:33.010
Pays attention to me?

18:33.012 --> 18:35.513
Do you people realize

18:35.515 --> 18:37.515
That I'm only
this many?

18:49.528 --> 18:51.662
Farkle, I need
to talk to you.

18:51.664 --> 18:53.498
I've been looking
all over for you.

18:58.036 --> 18:59.604
Farkle.

19:01.707 --> 19:03.407
Farkle's gone.

19:03.409 --> 19:06.010
He gave up the chess club.
He gave up the chemistry club.

19:06.012 --> 19:07.979
- What happened?
- You happened.

19:07.981 --> 19:09.714
You told me I was good.

19:09.716 --> 19:11.549
Well, I just auditioned
for the next play.

19:11.551 --> 19:12.984
Are you gonna be
in the next play?

19:12.986 --> 19:15.353
I'm not even allowed
to watch the next play.

19:16.321 --> 19:18.022
I'm sorry you stink.

19:19.491 --> 19:21.325
I'm sorry
I could never hurt you.

19:21.327 --> 19:22.960
I'm sorry you stink.

19:22.962 --> 19:25.096
- I heard you!
- Well, it was very important.

19:26.031 --> 19:27.865
( sighs )

19:27.867 --> 19:29.934
You made me think
I was this great actor.

19:29.936 --> 19:32.770
You filled me up
with confidence that I was
really special.

19:32.772 --> 19:35.706
You made me think
I could go after something
totally unrealistic.

19:35.708 --> 19:36.908
Farkle...

19:36.910 --> 19:38.876
Thank you.

19:42.014 --> 19:44.549
Mmmm...

19:45.617 --> 19:46.851
Mwuah!

19:54.059 --> 19:55.927
Well...

19:55.929 --> 19:57.495
That happened.

19:57.497 --> 19:58.729
Is it over?

19:59.665 --> 20:01.832
- Can we talk about this?
- No.

20:01.834 --> 20:03.768
Because that was
your first kiss

20:03.770 --> 20:05.469
And it was with farkle.

20:05.471 --> 20:07.405
- He missed.
- Still counts.

20:07.407 --> 20:08.539
Now for the rest
of your life

20:08.541 --> 20:09.874
When people ask you,
"hey, riley,

20:09.876 --> 20:12.376
Who was your first kiss?"
you're gonna have to say...

20:12.378 --> 20:13.544
Eyes, look your last.

20:13.546 --> 20:14.779
Oh, yeah!

20:17.749 --> 20:20.051
Arms, take your last embrace.

20:20.053 --> 20:22.787
And, lips, oh,
you the doors of breath,

20:22.789 --> 20:24.956
Seal with a righteous kiss.

20:24.958 --> 20:27.558
- Hi.
- Hi.

20:27.560 --> 20:28.693
How long you been here?

20:28.695 --> 20:30.661
Yeah, I saw the whole thing.

20:30.663 --> 20:31.929
I just can't believe
that little guy

20:31.931 --> 20:34.131
Stole my moment...
Again.

20:35.167 --> 20:37.535
You thought that
was your moment?

20:37.537 --> 20:38.970
No.

20:38.972 --> 20:41.005
Oh.

20:41.007 --> 20:42.640
My moment

20:42.642 --> 20:45.443
Will be  <i>my </i> moment.

20:47.946 --> 20:49.880
( sighs )

20:49.882 --> 20:51.749
( giggles )

20:59.057 --> 21:00.925
How you doing?

21:00.927 --> 21:03.527
I like that we end up
in situations like this.

21:12.070 --> 21:13.437
You're doing
the right thing,

21:13.439 --> 21:14.939
Returning the locket
to the store.

21:14.941 --> 21:16.207
I guess so.

21:16.209 --> 21:19.510
Maya, I know how much
you want a locket

21:19.512 --> 21:21.112
With a family inside it.

21:21.114 --> 21:22.113
You want the truth?

21:22.115 --> 21:26.884
My father hasn't sent me
anything in a long time.

21:26.886 --> 21:29.954
And the universe is
probably much too busy

21:29.956 --> 21:32.757
To notice whether or not
I'm doing the right thing.

21:51.476 --> 21:53.477
Hi.

21:53.479 --> 21:55.713
I think this belongs to you.

21:55.715 --> 21:57.515
Oh my gosh.

21:57.517 --> 21:58.949
I've been looking
all over for that.

21:58.951 --> 22:00.117
Thank you.

22:13.632 --> 22:15.066
Thank you.

22:16.168 --> 22:17.868
Never lose this.

22:26.511 --> 22:29.113
A cool universe, huh?

22:35.954 --> 22:37.088
( tapping )

22:44.029 --> 22:46.030
( sighs )
hi, auggie.

22:46.032 --> 22:47.298
Don't blow this.

22:51.837 --> 22:53.070
Hi.

22:53.072 --> 22:54.605
How you doing, honey?

22:54.607 --> 22:56.640
So...

22:56.642 --> 22:58.709
You remember that time
you were really mad at me?

22:58.711 --> 23:00.878
You mean right now?

23:00.880 --> 23:03.214
Yeah.  Yeah, that one.

23:04.583 --> 23:06.117
Listen, can I tell you
the truth about something?

23:08.787 --> 23:11.956
It doesn't really matter
what you make for dinner.

23:11.958 --> 23:14.925
It's that you are
in our house with me.

23:14.927 --> 23:17.094
Thank you for being
in our house with me.

23:19.631 --> 23:21.665
There's nowhere else
I'd rather be.

23:23.235 --> 23:24.335
Kiss kiss?

23:24.337 --> 23:26.003
Because you love me?

23:26.005 --> 23:27.004
Yes.

23:27.006 --> 23:29.140
And because
it quiets you down.
